The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 23 August is 65,080 (7,500.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 18 August, there were 2,574 new confirmed cases (296.7 new cases per 100,000). There is no change in cases compared to those confirmed in the previous week (seven days to 11 August).
